<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

00:24.791 --> 00:27.919
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.330 --> 00:32.298
[ Beeping ]

00:37.971 --> 00:39.939
## [Jazzy Solo ]

00:59.959 --> 01:01.927
[ Beeping ]

01:02.028 --> 01:03.928
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.230 --> 01:07.222
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:10.537 --> 01:12.937
<i>[ Frogs Croaking ]</i>

01:24.951 --> 01:27.181
This ghost town is gonna be great!

01:27.287 --> 01:29.278
''Now with 30% more gunfights.''

01:29.389 --> 01:31.414
And 40% more rootin'-tootin'.

01:31.524 --> 01:33.651
And the tumbleweeds tumble
at 2:00, 4:00 and 6:00...

01:33.760 --> 01:35.660
plus a midnight tumbling
on weekends.

01:35.762 --> 01:38.458
It's so sweet of you
to take us out like this, Homie.

01:38.565 --> 01:41.363
Come on, kids.
Three cheers for your father.

01:41.468 --> 01:43.368
- Hip, hip-
- Mom, don't.

01:43.470 --> 01:45.461
- Hip, hip-
- We heard you the first time.

01:45.572 --> 01:48.564
- Hip, hip-
- Hey, I'm trying to drive here.

01:48.675 --> 01:51.542
- Hey, Dad, that light says ''check engine.''
- [ Beeping ]

01:51.644 --> 01:54.511
Uh-oh. Tape must've fallen off.

01:55.849 --> 01:57.476
There. Problem solved.

01:57.584 --> 02:00.212
- [ Engine Backfires ]
- [ Lisa ] Oh, come on!

02:00.320 --> 02:04.188
Relax. She just needs a little lovin'.

02:04.290 --> 02:06.315
<i>- [ Engine Cranking ]
- [ Gasps ]</i>

02:07.827 --> 02:11.524
Ah, they remembered my birthday.

02:11.631 --> 02:14.327
Come on, come on, come on,
come on. Start, damn you!

02:14.434 --> 02:15.799
Start!

02:15.902 --> 02:18.166
## [ Singing ]

02:20.740 --> 02:23.538
[ Screaming ]

02:23.643 --> 02:26.407
[ Gasps ]

02:27.814 --> 02:29.714
Two hours?

02:29.816 --> 02:32.318
Why'd they build this
ghost town so far away?

02:38.858 --> 02:40.723
That's why everybody
does everything.

02:41.394 --> 02:43.760
[ Tires Screeching ]

02:47.700 --> 02:49.998
This should be very educational.

02:50.103 --> 02:52.264
I want you kids to pay attention.

02:52.372 --> 02:55.068
Founded by prostitutes in 1 849...

02:55.175 --> 02:57.871
and serviced by prostitute
express riders...

02:57.977 --> 03:01.743
who could bring in a fresh prostitute
from St.Joe in three days...

03:01.848 --> 03:04.408
Bloodbath Gulch
quickly became known...

03:04.517 --> 03:09.011
as a place where a trail hand could spend
a month's pay in three minutes.

03:09.122 --> 03:11.750
Three minutes!
[ Whistles ]

03:11.858 --> 03:14.656
I never realized history was so filthy.

03:14.761 --> 03:17.059
First on our tour is the whorehouse.

03:17.163 --> 03:20.360
Then we'll visit the cathouse,
the brothel, the bordello...

03:20.466 --> 03:22.661
and finally the old mission.

03:22.769 --> 03:26.569
- Oh, thank heaven!
- Lots of prostitutes in there.

03:31.211 --> 03:34.544
But there was more to the Old West
than just sex, folks.

03:34.647 --> 03:37.411
A lot more.
If you look off to your left...

03:37.517 --> 03:40.543
you'll see a real
Old West hitchin' post...

03:40.653 --> 03:45.920
<i>possibly used by bandits,
possibly during some exciting adventure.</i>

03:46.025 --> 03:49.984
And these planks below us
were often used as a sidewalk...

03:50.096 --> 03:53.827
by people who may
or may not have been bandits.

03:53.933 --> 03:57.266
[ Camera Shutters Clicking ]

03:57.370 --> 03:59.668
That's a keeper.

03:59.772 --> 04:01.797
- Uh, yes, sir?
- Do we have to listen to you?

04:01.908 --> 04:03.773
Well, no, you don't.

04:03.876 --> 04:06.037
But if you have any interest in history-

04:06.145 --> 04:08.670
- I'm done.
- [ Marge Mutters ]

04:10.283 --> 04:13.150
<i>##[ Ragtime Piano ]</i>

04:13.253 --> 04:16.380
<i>[ Bart ] Wow.! Have you ever seen
so many robot cowboys?</i>

04:16.488 --> 04:19.617
[ Screaming ]

04:20.860 --> 04:24.387
Hey, robot, get your fat
metal ass down here!

04:24.497 --> 04:27.330
First of all,
I'm not a robot.

04:27.433 --> 04:30.163
And second,
I got this metal ass in 'Nam...

04:30.270 --> 04:33.000
defending this country
for lazy jerks like you.

04:33.106 --> 04:35.006
Now what'll you have, partner?

04:35.108 --> 04:37.941
Let's see. One, two, three-
Six whiskeys.

04:38.044 --> 04:41.775
- All right!
- We only serve sarsaparilla, mac. No alcohol.

04:41.881 --> 04:44.247
- [ Groans ]
- You can get drunk when we get home.

04:44.350 --> 04:46.250
Duh.

04:46.352 --> 04:49.321
[ Robot Voice ]
Hey, these cards are marked.

04:49.422 --> 04:51.447
Now look what you've done.

04:51.557 --> 04:55.254
I'm sorry. I don't know
what came over me.

04:55.361 --> 04:57.852
Let's forget this
whole thing happened.

04:57.964 --> 04:59.932
What the heck is this?
A tea party?

05:00.033 --> 05:02.297
Somebody kill somebody!
[ Grunts ]

05:04.604 --> 05:08.335
- [ Screams ]
- What is it with you and robots?

05:10.243 --> 05:14.270
- [ Grunts ]
- ## [ Ragtime Piano ]

05:16.949 --> 05:21.113
<i>- Whoa!
- ##[ Ragtime Piano Continues ]</i>

05:21.220 --> 05:24.121
Whoo! Hello, sweet cheeks!

05:24.223 --> 05:26.487
[ Grunts ]

05:26.592 --> 05:29.891
- Look who's a little cowgirl.
- [ Gurgling ]

05:29.996 --> 05:32.362
Hey, Mom, look what I got!

05:32.465 --> 05:34.592
<i>Oh, that's cute.!</i>

05:34.701 --> 05:36.828
[ Laughs ]
Did you get it in the souvenir shop?

05:36.936 --> 05:39.496
No, that security guard
is handing 'em out.

05:40.740 --> 05:43.004
[ Groans ]

05:51.351 --> 05:54.081
Uh-oh. Better run for cover, partners.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.451
Some varmints are havin' a shootout.

05:56.556 --> 05:58.547
Yee-haw!

05:58.658 --> 06:00.922
- You stole my prostitute!
- Missed me!

06:01.027 --> 06:04.656
- Die, yellow belly!
- [ Grunts ]

06:04.764 --> 06:06.356
Bang-bang!

06:13.306 --> 06:15.934
Uh, which way's the gunfight?

06:16.042 --> 06:19.307
- [ All Laughing ]
- There's Old Curly.

06:19.412 --> 06:21.937
<i>He played the town preacher
until we laid him off.</i>

06:22.048 --> 06:25.415
But he still hangs around.

06:25.518 --> 06:28.043
Help me, please. I'm sick.

06:28.154 --> 06:30.281
- [ Laughing ]
- Homer!

06:30.390 --> 06:33.052
But it's funny, Marge.
The guy's sick.

06:33.159 --> 06:37.687
[ Groans, Gurgling ]

06:37.797 --> 06:39.697
Uh, shouldn't we help him?

06:39.799 --> 06:41.699
He knows what he's doing.

06:43.202 --> 06:46.262
<i>##[ Piano Playing ]</i>

06:46.372 --> 06:50.240
Ahh. Can't get a good sarsaparilla
like this back in Springfield.

06:50.343 --> 06:52.243
It ''angries'' up the blood.

06:52.345 --> 06:55.246
- You like it, huh?
- Up yours!

06:55.348 --> 06:58.875
<i>[ Truck Horn Honking ]</i>

06:58.985 --> 07:01.613
Can I go to the bathroom
before we leave?

07:01.721 --> 07:05.680
<i>We gotta get home. I don't want to miss
Inside the Actor's Studio.</i>

07:05.792 --> 07:07.987
Tonight it's F. Murray Abraham.

07:08.094 --> 07:12.053
- But I really need to-
- F. Murray Abraham!

07:12.165 --> 07:15.566
- ## [ Homer Whistling ]
- [ Grampa Groaning ]

07:17.036 --> 07:19.129
There's a rest area.
Pull over.

07:19.238 --> 07:21.399
Can't stop now.
We're making great time.

07:21.507 --> 07:25.637
[ Grampa Muttering ]
Can I go behind a tree?

07:25.745 --> 07:27.804
What are you? An animal?

07:27.914 --> 07:30.883
[ Homer] Whoever keeps saying
''please stop'' back there better quit it!

07:30.983 --> 07:35.181
- [ Grampa Groans ]
- [ Homer] Wow. Get a load of that toilet.

07:35.288 --> 07:38.917
Please go back! You can make it
my birthday present.

07:39.025 --> 07:41.118
We're almost home, Dad.

07:41.227 --> 07:43.491
Only a couple more times
over the horizon.

07:43.596 --> 07:45.223
But I might explode!

07:45.331 --> 07:47.561
- You just sit back and relax.
- [ Whimpering ]

07:47.667 --> 07:51.398
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to my old dad.

07:51.504 --> 07:53.404
Oh, dear God!

07:53.506 --> 07:55.599
This man's kidneys have exploded.

07:55.708 --> 07:57.938
- There's nothing left.
- Oh, no!

07:58.044 --> 08:00.342
Yeah, that's what happens
when you get older.

08:00.446 --> 08:03.574
It's one of those natural things.
Beautiful in its way.

08:03.683 --> 08:07.642
Uh, actually his kidneys were fine yesterday
when he had his annual checkup.

08:07.753 --> 08:11.348
Excuse me, Doctor. I think I know
a little something about medicine.

08:11.457 --> 08:16.156
Homer, with all due respect, this X-ray
reveals a textbook kidney blowout.

08:16.262 --> 08:19.095
Which would explain
those loud pops you heard.

08:19.198 --> 08:21.996
<i>So you're saying
I don't need a new muffler?</i>

08:22.101 --> 08:26.765
I don't feel so good.
Maybe I oughta eat something.

08:26.873 --> 08:30.866
Oh, I'm afraid your eating days are over.
[ Laughing ]

08:30.977 --> 08:35.880
[ Laughing, Groans ]

08:39.184 --> 08:41.813
How long do I have to live, Doc?

08:41.921 --> 08:44.947
[ Laughs ]
I'm amazed you're alive now.

08:45.057 --> 08:48.288
Oh, I blame myself for this.

08:48.394 --> 08:50.692
We all blame you.

08:50.796 --> 08:53.765
Come on, Doc. There's gotta be
something I can do to help my dad.

08:53.866 --> 08:58.166
- Well, you could give him a kidney.
- A kidney? Okay, fine.

08:58.271 --> 09:01.729
You see, the waiting list
for a kidney is very long, and-

09:01.841 --> 09:03.672
I said fine.

09:03.776 --> 09:06.643
What is it about the word ''sure''
you don't understand?

09:06.746 --> 09:08.941
Oh, thank you, Son.

09:09.048 --> 09:13.417
Hmm, I'll take the left one.
It's good and springy.

09:13.519 --> 09:16.955
Though the right one's
not without its charms.

09:18.691 --> 09:23.219
Pork chops, sloppy joes,
hot dogs and... pork chops!

09:23.329 --> 09:26.059
Well, Dr. Hibbert said
you have to build up your strength.

09:26.165 --> 09:29.862
Besides, nothing's too good
for a wonderful, generous man like you.

09:29.969 --> 09:32.767
<i>- Well, that's what I always thought, but somehow-
- Check it out, Dad.</i>

09:32.872 --> 09:35.340
I rented all your favorite
gorilla movies.

09:35.441 --> 09:38.342
<i>Gorilla Squadron,
Gorilla Island VI.</i>

09:38.444 --> 09:41.936
<i>[ Gasps ] Apes-A-Poppin;!
Whoo, the airline version.</i>

09:42.048 --> 09:45.381
- Can I fluff your pillow?
- Nothing's too good for me.

09:45.484 --> 09:48.942
Ahh, I'm the luckiest man
in the world...

09:49.055 --> 09:50.955
now that Lou Gehrig's dead.

09:52.725 --> 09:54.625
Well, I gotta hand it to you, Homer.

09:54.727 --> 09:57.093
You're really brave to go
through with this operation.

09:57.196 --> 10:00.563
It's not an operation, Moe.
The doctor says it's just a procedure.

10:00.666 --> 10:03.226
No, no, no. Makin' polenta-
that's a procedure.

10:03.336 --> 10:06.362
You're talkin' about deadly,
life-threatening surgery here.

10:06.472 --> 10:09.202
Really? Do you think it's dangerous?

10:09.308 --> 10:12.004
Oh, yeah.
Even if you survive the operation-

10:12.111 --> 10:14.739
Procedure! Deadly procedure!

10:14.847 --> 10:17.042
Whatever. The point is,
with only one kidney...

10:17.149 --> 10:19.640
you won't be able to drink
yourself stupid no more.

10:19.752 --> 10:21.344
Now you're just tryin' to scare me.

10:21.454 --> 10:24.651
Plus they'll put you on one of those
organ donor sucker lists.

10:24.757 --> 10:29.854
Everybody who wants an eyeball or a spine
or a vestigial tail will be after you.

10:29.962 --> 10:33.159
<i>- But I don't want that.
- Listen, I'm just gonna get right to the point here.</i>

10:33.265 --> 10:37.292
Can I have your buttocks? I mean,
if you die. They look pretty comfortable.

10:37.403 --> 10:40.304
- Yeah, I guess.
- And are those your original lips?

10:40.406 --> 10:44.274
Well, actually, I- Hey!
Quit harvesting me with your eyes!

10:44.377 --> 10:46.277
[ Grunts ]

10:46.379 --> 10:49.280
Oh, yeah. That would look
so good on me.

10:50.449 --> 10:52.349
Marge, I've been thinking.

10:52.451 --> 10:55.284
What if instead of donating
one of my old, worn-out kidneys...

10:55.388 --> 10:57.720
I gave Grampa that
artificial kidney I invented?

10:57.823 --> 11:01.190
Oh, Homer, that was just a beer can
with a whistle glued to it.

11:01.293 --> 11:04.888
Oh, but I don't want them
cutting up my soft, supple body.

11:04.997 --> 11:08.160
Why didn't somebody tell me
what I was volunteering for?

11:08.267 --> 11:10.531
This is everybody's fault but mine.

11:10.636 --> 11:12.968
I know you're scared, Homie.

11:13.072 --> 11:16.564
But remember why you're doing this.
It's for your father.

11:16.676 --> 11:20.305
<i>The man who raised you
and nurtured you.</i>

11:20.413 --> 11:24.577
''Jack and Jill went up the hill and-

11:24.684 --> 11:27.244
Jill came tumbling after.''
The end. Good night.

11:27.353 --> 11:30.322
Is that the sameJack
from ''Jack and the Beanstalk''?

11:30.423 --> 11:32.914
- You know, Son, I believe it is.
- And Jack Sprat?

11:33.025 --> 11:36.153
- Is that him too?
- Sure. Why not? Good night.

11:36.262 --> 11:38.492
Is he the same as ''Jack be nimble''...

11:38.597 --> 11:41.225
and Jack Frost and LittleJack Horner?

11:41.333 --> 11:44.097
Say, how about a little NyQuil?

11:44.203 --> 11:46.262
[ Gulps ]
All gone.

11:46.372 --> 11:49.307
- [ Snoring ]
- Ah, I love you, Son.

11:49.408 --> 11:52.104
I owe Dad so much.

11:52.211 --> 11:58.013
Those bedtime stories began my lifelong
love affair with the printed word.

11:58.117 --> 12:02.019
Well, giving him a kidney is
a wonderful way to show him how you feel.

12:02.121 --> 12:04.419
You're right, Marge.
I'll do it.

12:04.523 --> 12:08.152
But if I die during the operation,
will you do one thing for me?

12:08.260 --> 12:12.356
- Oh, anything, sweetheart.
- Blow up the hospital.

12:12.465 --> 12:17.630
Hmm. Well, I said I'd do it,
so I guess I'll have to.

12:17.737 --> 12:19.705
That's my girl.

12:19.805 --> 12:21.830
[ Groans ]

12:24.310 --> 12:26.335
<i>[ Woman On P.A.]
Doc Martens to Podiatry.</i>

12:26.445 --> 12:29.710
- ''Liability waiver''?
- Don't read it.Just sign it.

12:29.815 --> 12:31.976
Yeah, but all these skulls
and crossbones on here.

12:32.084 --> 12:34.075
I don't usually sign stuff like that.

12:34.186 --> 12:36.586
It simply says you won't
hold us responsible...

12:36.689 --> 12:38.850
if you die as a result
of gross negligence.

12:38.958 --> 12:41.153
It's a standard form.

12:41.260 --> 12:43.160
[ Groans ]

12:43.262 --> 12:45.787
[ Machines Beeping ]

12:45.898 --> 12:48.366
I love you, Son.

12:48.467 --> 12:50.492
I love you, Dad.

12:53.439 --> 12:57.739
Now don't you fellas worry.
This'll all be over soon.

12:57.843 --> 13:01.301
And-What the-

13:01.413 --> 13:03.244
We gotta get rid of that window.

13:03.349 --> 13:08.184
- Where'd he go?
- [ Grunting ]

13:12.725 --> 13:15.489
I can't imagine Dad
running away like this.

13:15.594 --> 13:17.494
Leaving his father to die?

13:17.596 --> 13:20.121
Even I wouldn't do that.
And I'm America's bad boy.

13:20.232 --> 13:24.862
It's a heartbreaking situation.
[ Chuckles Slowly ]

13:24.970 --> 13:27.734
- Am I dead yet?
- No.

13:27.840 --> 13:29.705
- How about now?
- No!

13:29.809 --> 13:32.607
- Now?
- I'll tell you when you're dead, Grampa.

13:32.711 --> 13:35.771
- Thank you.
- [ Grunting ]

13:43.989 --> 13:45.923
Phew.

13:51.363 --> 13:54.560
I'm not worthy to live
among civilized people.

13:54.667 --> 13:57.659
[ Men Coughing, Murmuring ]

13:57.770 --> 14:00.466
Even those guys look
too civilized for me.

14:00.573 --> 14:03.633
<i>[ Seagull Squawking ]</i>

14:03.742 --> 14:07.143
[ Gasps ] I can live at sea!
The sea forgives all!

14:07.246 --> 14:11.876
Not like those mean old mountains.
I hate them so much.

14:11.984 --> 14:13.781
<i>[ Wind Gusting ]</i>

14:13.886 --> 14:16.753
- [ Men Groaning ]
- The sea won't stand for this.

14:22.328 --> 14:26.264
Excuse me. I'm fleeing in shame,
and I'd like to look my best.

14:29.101 --> 14:33.800
Um, can I be a mate on your ship?
Preferably first mate.

14:33.906 --> 14:39.242
<i>Well, if you look closely, you'll see
this is a taffy shop shaped like a ship.</i>

14:39.345 --> 14:43.213
Oh, I like taffy,
but I don't deserve taffy.

14:43.315 --> 14:45.442
<i>##[ Ukulele ]</i>

14:45.551 --> 14:48.042
- Hey, hey!
- What's that?

14:48.153 --> 14:50.246
Krusty here to cheer you up...

14:50.356 --> 14:53.519
as part of the hospital's
Last Laugh program.

14:53.626 --> 14:55.321
Last laugh?

14:55.427 --> 14:58.624
So, how about that
hospital food, huh?

14:58.731 --> 15:01.359
I wouldn't know.
I'm not allowed to eat.

15:01.467 --> 15:05.403
Okay. Well, let's have
a look at the old chart.

15:05.504 --> 15:10.100
Oh, boy! Ooh, looks like
we're both short on time.

15:10.209 --> 15:12.473
So I'll go to the big finish.

15:12.578 --> 15:16.014
## [ Singing ]

15:16.115 --> 15:19.278
## [ Ends ]

15:19.385 --> 15:21.148
Feel better.

15:21.253 --> 15:23.517
Come back, Doctor.

15:23.622 --> 15:27.422
<i>[ Horn Blowing ]</i>

15:27.526 --> 15:29.653
A tramp steamer!
That's perfect!

15:29.762 --> 15:33.027
[ Grunting ]

15:33.132 --> 15:35.532
[ Groans ]

15:35.634 --> 15:38.603
I'd like to apply for a job.
Any job.

15:38.704 --> 15:41.002
If you don't have a captain,
I could be that.

15:41.106 --> 15:43.904
Arr! What other ships have you been on?

15:44.009 --> 15:47.274
I've been on that one.
The taffy shop.

15:47.379 --> 15:50.007
Good enough.

15:50.115 --> 15:52.208
[ Both Grunting ]

15:52.318 --> 15:54.809
Welcome aboard the ship of...

15:54.920 --> 15:57.184
lost souls.

15:57.289 --> 15:59.189
<i>The name on the back
says Honeybunch.</i>

15:59.291 --> 16:02.055
Yarr, I've been meaning
to paint over that.

16:02.161 --> 16:04.755
Now come and meet
the rest of the damned.

16:04.863 --> 16:08.697
Did I mention they're...
lost souls?

16:08.801 --> 16:12.328
- Well, actually you did.
- Yarr, yarr.

16:16.475 --> 16:18.443
<i>[ Ship Creaking ]</i>

16:18.544 --> 16:23.880
<i>[ French Accent ] Ah, another lost soul
has joined our world-weary ensemble.</i>

16:23.983 --> 16:27.316
- Hey, who are you guys?
- [ Laughing ]

16:27.419 --> 16:31.685
Who are we? No one.
Where are we sailing? Nowhere.

16:31.790 --> 16:34.918
Do we even exist?
Who knows?

16:35.027 --> 16:37.086
Hey, let me off this thing.

16:37.196 --> 16:40.893
[ English Accent ] Oh, don't listen to him.
We exist all right.

16:41.000 --> 16:44.800
We wander the seven seas
trying to forget.

16:44.903 --> 16:47.497
- Forget what?
- Oh, boy. Here we go.

16:47.606 --> 16:52.441
My story of jilted love
is long and bittersweet.

16:52.544 --> 16:56.207
If anyone has to go to the bathroom, go.
I don't want you walking around during my story.

16:56.315 --> 16:58.408
My story's better.
It has tigers.

16:58.517 --> 17:01.782
- ## [ Concertina ]
- I was born into wretched poverty.

17:01.887 --> 17:04.185
So one day I stole a loaf of bread...

17:04.289 --> 17:07.554
put it in the freezer until it was very hard,
then robbed a bank with it.

17:07.659 --> 17:09.183
[ Gasps ]

17:11.262 --> 17:15.529
And when Mr. Dinkley
saw what I had done...

17:15.634 --> 17:18.728
I was banned from the car wash forever.

17:18.837 --> 17:20.737
Forever? How awful!

17:20.839 --> 17:22.739
I would have killed Dinkley for that.

17:22.840 --> 17:27.904
As you can see, we're a contemptible lot
of cads, bounders and tiger stabbers.

17:28.012 --> 17:30.811
Come, stranger.
Join our circle of infamy.

17:30.916 --> 17:34.511
Tell us your story of ennui.

17:34.620 --> 17:39.023
Well, back on land
my name was Homer Simpson.

17:39.124 --> 17:41.649
And I guess it is here too.

17:41.760 --> 17:43.660
I promised my dad one of my kidneys...

17:43.762 --> 17:46.925
but I chickened out at the last minute
and left him on his deathbed.

17:47.032 --> 17:49.557
- Good Lord!
- Oh, how could you!

17:49.668 --> 17:54.401
- I think I'm going to be sick.
- I stole this accordion from a blind monkey.

17:54.506 --> 17:58.135
But you! [ Spits ]
You disgust even me!

17:58.243 --> 18:01.007
- Well, yeah, I know-
- [ Grunting ]

18:01.113 --> 18:03.513
[ Screams ]

18:06.485 --> 18:11.115
- [ Horn Blowing ]
- That's the last time I trust
the strangest people on Earth.

18:15.661 --> 18:17.629
[ Coughing ]

18:17.729 --> 18:20.926
Even the sea won't forgive me.

18:21.033 --> 18:24.196
That's the best sand castle
we've ever built, Dad!

18:24.303 --> 18:26.294
We make a great team, Son.

18:26.405 --> 18:31.707
Oh, I wish I had that kind
of relationship with my father.

18:31.810 --> 18:35.075
[ Sniffs ]
Or my kids.

18:35.180 --> 18:39.617
Well, I guess it's up to me
to take the first step.

18:39.718 --> 18:42.687
- [ Crying ]
- Hey!

18:42.788 --> 18:44.312
<i>[ Woman On P.A.]
Dr. Bombay, come right away.</i>

18:44.423 --> 18:47.620
All right. This is it.
No more living in shame.

18:47.726 --> 18:51.594
I'm going to show my family
the kind of man I really am.

18:53.298 --> 18:55.766
[ Whimpering ]

18:55.868 --> 18:58.302
All right. I'm gonna-

18:58.403 --> 19:00.462
[ Whimpering ]

19:03.075 --> 19:07.011
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Machine Beeping ]

19:07.112 --> 19:09.876
Aren't you going to give him
the last rites?

19:09.982 --> 19:14.476
That's Catholic, Marge. You might as well
ask me to do a voodoo dance.

19:14.586 --> 19:17.749
Dr. Hibbert, I thought you'd located
another kidney for Grampa.

19:17.856 --> 19:21.986
Larry Hagman took it.
He's got five of them now. And three hearts.

19:22.094 --> 19:25.154
We didn't want to give them to him,
but he overpowered us.

19:25.264 --> 19:30.031
Don't worry about old Grampa.
I'm going to a better place.

19:30.135 --> 19:32.831
- Shelbyville Hospital!
- [ Alarm Beeping ]

19:32.938 --> 19:36.339
Oh, who am I kidding?
I'm a goner.

19:36.441 --> 19:38.341
<i>[ Homer ]
No,you're not, Dad.</i>

19:38.443 --> 19:40.172
- Homer!
- Dad!

19:40.279 --> 19:43.214
- Son!
- I'm sorry, Dad.

19:43.315 --> 19:47.115
The way I behaved was shameful.
I guess fear made me run away.

19:47.219 --> 19:50.120
But love made me come back.

19:50.222 --> 19:52.690
Bless you, Son.

19:52.791 --> 19:56.124
I knew you'd come through for me.

19:56.228 --> 20:00.221
Now, Homer, this may sting
just a tiny bit, but-

20:03.135 --> 20:06.901
- Oh, son of a-
- [ Panting, Whimpering ]

20:09.408 --> 20:11.899
Oh, dear.

20:12.010 --> 20:14.501
[ Screaming ]

20:14.613 --> 20:18.640
Phew! Boy, that- Ow!

20:19.751 --> 20:22.276
<i>- [ Homer Groaning ]
- He's waking up!</i>

20:22.387 --> 20:25.117
Oh, Homie,
I'm so glad you're all right.

20:25.224 --> 20:28.193
[ Groaning ]

20:28.293 --> 20:31.729
Try not to move, Dad.
You swallowed a lot of motor oil.

20:31.830 --> 20:34.355
I'm sorry I ran off again.

20:34.466 --> 20:37.833
Oh, I guess Dad
must be dead by now.

20:37.936 --> 20:39.836
When I get better...

20:39.938 --> 20:43.271
and after I've built those shelves
for the kitchen, we'll visit his grave.

20:43.375 --> 20:47.277
<i>Grave nothin;!
I never felt more alive.!</i>

20:47.379 --> 20:49.279
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Bones Cracking ]

20:49.381 --> 20:51.611
Oh, boy,
I shouldn't have done that.

20:51.717 --> 20:55.619
It's a miracle!
You recovered!

20:55.721 --> 20:58.656
[ Nervous Laughing ]

20:58.757 --> 21:01.726
What? What?

21:01.827 --> 21:03.658
Hey!

21:03.762 --> 21:07.323
While we were setting your broken bones
and putting your blood back in...

21:07.432 --> 21:10.765
we helped ourselves to a kidney
and gave it to your father.

21:10.869 --> 21:13.235
You butchers!
Give it back! Give me that-

21:13.338 --> 21:17.968
[ Laughing ]
Na-na-na-na-na-na!

21:18.076 --> 21:20.271
Don't you dance out that door, you-

21:20.379 --> 21:22.279
I'll get my kidney back, old man!

21:22.381 --> 21:24.281
You have to sleep sometime.

21:24.383 --> 21:28.479
I know you're a little peeved at Grampa,
Dad, but you've done a wonderful thing.

21:28.587 --> 21:31.385
Yes. You've shortened
your life significantly...

21:31.490 --> 21:34.618
so someone else can have
a slight extension of theirs.

21:34.726 --> 21:38.389
Yeah, I guess you're right.
Give me a hug.

21:38.497 --> 21:41.933
Ah, I don't need two kidneys.

21:42.034 --> 21:46.562
I have everything I need
right here. Hmm.

21:46.672 --> 21:49.300
[ Laughing ]
Dad, you're tickling me.

21:49.408 --> 21:52.309
Yes, tickling.

21:52.411 --> 21:54.072
Hmm?

22:39.558 --> 22:43.961
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

